<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 04 at 4:45PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of central Madison,
central Beaverhead and central Gallatin Counties through 515 PM
MDT...
At 443 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms
moving east at 55 mph across central portions of Beaverhead,
Madison, and Gallatin Counties.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Virginia City, Ennis, Jeffers, Big Sky and Cameron.
This includes the following highways...
Interstate 15 between mile markers 48  and 50 .
Highway 191 between mile markers 38 and 70.
Highway 287 between mile markers 28 and 51.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
